  "text": "Secretoneurin assay-Human plasma treated with EDTA as an anticoagulant was frozen and stored at −70°C prior to assay. The biologically active secretoneurin fragment of human SCG2 (TNEIVEEQYTPQSLATLESVFQELGKLTGPNNQ) was measured by RIA, as previously described [CITATION_1] with a rabbit polyclonal antibody directed against synthetic human secretoneurin (SCG2 154-165 ) and iodination on the endogenous Tyr. The assay sensitivity in plasma was <40 pmol/L, with a reference range of <220 pM (<0.22 nM).",
